> To make these loaded tacos, you'll glaze tender chicken and shredded red cabbage in an
> umami-rich blend of hoisin mixed with sweet Thai chili sauce. Nestle that
> savory-sweet chicken into warm flour tortillas and top with a bright,
> refreshing cucumber-scallion for a quick weeknight meal in a speedy 20 minutes.

== Cucumber-Scallion Relish ==

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites
from greens. Trim and finely dice half the @cucumber{1}(trimmed and finely diced).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine scallion greens, diced cucumber,
@rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Set aside,
stirring occasionally.

== Hoisin Shrimp ==

Open package of @shrimp{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

> Shrimp is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp and scallion whites; season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until beginning to brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}, @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon},
@sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until sauce has thickened and shrimp is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more.
Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

== Assembly ==

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and
pliable, about ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates; fill with hoisin shrimp and as much cucumber relish
(draining first) as you like. Garnish with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} and serve.